cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is about image captioning, which involves computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new model architecture that uses attention mechanisms, which is a common technique in natural language processing, suggesting that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper deals with multimodal data, combining visual and textual information, which suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category.
